American adventurer Steve Fossett, backed by Virgin, is set for a solo, non-stop flight around the globe aboard the GlobalFlyer.
Despite GPS malfunctions and a slow start, Fossett remains optimistic as he navigates at 45,000 feet.
Branson, funding the project, hopes for advancements in aviation technology.
The mission, expected to last 60-80 hours, aims to inspire future innovations in fuel efficiency.
With Branson monitoring the journey, Fossett faces challenges but remains determined to achieve this historic feat.
The world watches as Fossett embarks on this daring adventure, pushing the boundaries of aviation.
